The treaty references annexes repeatedly, though none are included in this file. On another note, Article 16.9 outlines the creation of a tribunal of non-party nationals for dispute resolution. I marked this as a Yes for delegation 1. Obligation 3 is a yes because the created tribunal for resolving disputes is allowed to award recompense to parties that have been wronged in violation of the treaty at the expense of the party who violates said treaty.
Obligation 2 is marked as a Y, because the agreement stipulates that data on the implementation of the treaty will be supplied to either part upon request.
Compliance monitoring is a maybe, the Joint Commission established by the parties is in charge of overseeing implementation of this treaty.
Interesting note: this treaty references the term "man month", which I looked up, it means the amount of work one person can accomplish in a month, it isn't an amount of time.
